title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1988-12-31
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll-> Franklin's Tower, Wang Dang Doodle*, West L.A. Fadeaway*, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Cold Rain & Snow, Cassidy-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Sugar Magnolia*-> Touch Of Gray*-> Women Are Smarter*-> Terrapin Station-> Drums**-> Space-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin -> Watchtower-> Morning Dew-> Sugar mag Reprise-> Sunshine Daydream, Wharf Rat, Goin Down the Road, Saturday Night

Other Artist(s): * w/ Clarence Clemons on sax, ** Baba Olatunji, Sikiru Adepoju and Kitaro

reviews.review_text: New years!!! ...My one and only new years show and I almost didn't make it however at the  last minute my sister scored 2 MIRACLE tickets...We reacted like 2 kids in a candy shop and the show was great with the special guests and got to meet Bill Graham for the 1st time and he was great, a real class act...All in all a great run except for the frigid temps in the Bay area that year!!!
